  "prompt": "How do I clear a blocked nose when in a supine position?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to help clear a blocked nose while lying down:\n\n1. Nasal Irrigation\n- Use a saline nasal spray\n- Gently tilt your head and spray into each nostril\n- This can help loosen mucus and clear congestion\n\n2. Head Position Techniques\n- Prop your head up with an extra pillow\n- Slightly elevate your head to help drainage\n- Use a wedge pillow for better angle\n\n3. Breathing Exercises\n- Alternate nostril breathing\n- Deep breathing with controlled exhales\n- Gentle blowing techniques\n\n4. Steam Inhalation\n- Use a portable steam inhaler\n- Place a warm, damp washcloth over your face\n- Breathe slowly and deeply\n\n5. Decongestant Methods\n- Use over-the-counter nasal decongestant drops\n- Take oral decongestant medications\n- Apply vapor rub near nostrils\n\n6. Gentle Massage\n- Softly massage the sides of your nose\n- Press pressure points around nasal area\n- Use gentle circular motions\n\n7. Hydration\n- Drink warm liquids\n- Stay well-hydrated to thin mucus\n\nAlways consult a healthcare professional if congestion persists or worsens.",
